The wilderness, both wild and free,
In every rustle, spirit's plea,
Where life unfolds in sacred space,
In nature’s arms, we find our grace.

With every heartbeat, life ignites,
In nature’s hold, the world ignites,
Together, we embrace the earth,
And in its quiet, find rebirth.

- Emile Gaboriau
